<p>
<ul>
<li><b>Enabled</b> – Boolean value indicating whether or not this channel should report data.</li></ul>
<p>
<ul>
<li><b>InputType</b> – Corresponds to AC- vs. DC-coupling. InputType can be derived from RangeIndex; values 0-7 for RangeIndex indicate AC-Coupling (InputType 0) and 8-15 indicate DC-Coupling (InputType 1). See Table 1: Scaling. Both values are required to be included in the configuration file. Fast Inputs Only. </li></ul>
